{"user_message": {"title": "Architecture Review — 2026-05-29: ADR 0005 (Money Formatting) Re-affirmed, Still Unexecuted", "content": "## Verdict\nThis week's review found **no new architectural decision needed** — but a **standing one (ADR 0005) is overdue and drift is accumulating**. Re-affirmed against the live `ai-bookkeeper` tree; addendum appended to `docs/adr/0005-money-formatting-consolidation.md`.\n\n## ADR — Consolidate money formatting onto one shared kernel (re-affirmed)\n\n**Context.** The ADR-blessed, drift-free formatter `formatMoney` (ADR 0004) is **still orphaned — 0 real consumers** (only the ledger barrel re-exports it). Every visible balance still flows through `src/lib/format.ts` `formatCurrency`/`formatSignedCurrency`: **USD-hardcoded, no `roundMoney` normalization, no fail-loud**. A third path (`WealthScoreCard.tsx:195` inline `$…M` `toFixed`) persists. ADR 0004's guarantee — *what the user sees is provably what the ledger stored* — remains unrealized in the product.\n\n**Decision (unchanged).** Promote money primitives (`round`/`arithmetic`/`format`) to a shared kernel `src/lib/money/`; make `formatMoney` the single formatter behind back-compat `formatCurrency`/`formatSignedCurrency` wrappers; re-point all consumers; add a lint guardrail forbidding raw `$`/`toFixed` on money outside the kernel. **No new primitive — adoption + consolidation only.**\n\n**New evidence this cycle.**\n- **Fresh drift:** v0.7.0 added a new ledger UI, `LedgerExplorer.tsx`. `TransactionsCard` is now a thin wrapper; the real render moved to `LedgerExplorer.tsx:222` — and was wired **straight to the un-normalized formatter**. A brand-new surface attached to the wrong path this cycle = exactly the regression the guardrail prevents.\n- **Kernel home reinforced:** v0.7.0 introduced `src/lib/data/` (data-layer boundary). There's now a precedent for shared non-feature libs under `src/lib/`, so `src/lib/money/` sits naturally beside it. The \"make `@/features/ledger` the kernel\" alternative is weaker than ever.\n\n**Consequences.** Drift-free/currency-aware/fail-loud display becomes real app-wide; one money authority instead of three; feature→feature coupling on money removed; guardrail stops regression. Cost is a mechanical 6-file move + re-point of 8 consumers, shippable incrementally.\n\n## Current un-normalized consumers (8 files)\n`benchmarks/{BenchmarksCard, ComparisonBar}`, `customers/{CustomerPanel, MergeCandidatesCard}`, `tax-credits/{EvidenceChip, TaxCreditsCard}`, `wealth-score/WealthScoreCard`, `ledger/LedgerExplorer`.\n\n## Task breakdown (refreshed — 11 pts)\n| # | Task | Pts |\n|---|------|-----|\n| 1 | Create `src/lib/money/` kernel; move `round.ts`+`arithmetic.ts`+`format.ts`+tests; add barrel; keep `features/ledger/lib` re-exporting one release. Suite stays green at current baseline (9 test files). | 3 |\n| 2 | Reimplement `src/lib/format.ts` `formatCurrency`/`formatSignedCurrency` as wrappers over `formatMoney(_, \"USD\")`; preserve `+`/`−` (U+2212) semantics; golden-string tests. | 2 |\n| 3 | Re-point the 8 money-render components (ledger target is now `LedgerExplorer.tsx:222`, not `TransactionsCard`); delete dead paths. | 2 |\n| 4 | Replace `WealthScoreCard.tsx:195` inline `$…M/$…K` with kernel `formatMoneyCompact` (or `Intl` compact) + tests. | 2 |\n| 5 | Add lint guardrail forbidding raw money templates/`toFixed` outside `src/lib/money`. | 2 |\n\n**Total: 11 pts** (was 12 — ADR 0006 already resolved the old Task 6 lint blocker; dropped). **Recommendation: greenlight execution this release — it has now slipped one full cycle while drift grew.**", "content_type": "success", "priority": "high"}}

